      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For a smooth finish, you'll want to use a good joint compound and a proper taping technique. First, apply your tape, making sure to press it down firmly with a taping knife. Then, let that layer dry completely before applying your first coat of mud. Don't rush this, as a slow, steady approach is key to avoiding those tell-tale lines.",
