    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. one more thing—if i notice any small gaps or holes that seem to have opened up in the corners after the first coat dries, should i just fill them with more mud or is there something else i should be looking for? sometimes it feels like they just keep appearing in those dark spots behind the vanity.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If you see small gaps or holes appearing after the first coat, don't just blindly shove more mud in there, as that just makes a bigger mess. You need to figure out *why* the gap is there, which is often a sign that the tape wasn't fully pressed down or that there's a slight imperfection in the drywall itself. Sometimes, a little bit of joint compound mixed with a little water, just a thin smear, can help fill those tiny voids before you go back to the main mud.",
      "source": "target",
